24/09 - They requested the perf of Alto.
We are going to give the perf vs Long using Due Diligence Reports -> Attribution report
Divisor=Nav, Leveraged Yes, Ramp up yes, Period Daily, Total only

For the alpha we take alto (not low vol) from alpha alto, stop the code to get the daily alpha from alto and universe.
We stopped at end of august
Be careful the df is cummulative, what we give is daily

We also gave the universe member (just europe and US):

SELECT T2.ticker FROM product_universe T1 JOIN product T2 on T1.product_id=T2.id
JOIN exchange T3 on T2.exchange_id=T3.id JOIN country T4 on T3.country_id=T4.id WHERE end_date is NULL and continent='EMEA' order by ticker;

SELECT T2.ticker FROM product_universe T1 JOIN product T2 on T1.product_id=T2.id
JOIN exchange T3 on T2.exchange_id=T3.id JOIN country T4 on T3.country_id=T4.id WHERE end_date is NULL and continent='AMER' order by ticker;

They also requested the EOM position for alto, we gave until end of may (I added the function find_position_alto)
I removed options and index not SPX and SXXP, + all long<300k


